# eAutomate sync doctrine

## One-way ingest

- All `npm run sync:*` scripts copy **eAutomate → Zap Postgres** only.
- **Sync never writes back to eAutomate.** Do not tell users sync will update eAutomate.
- Zap UI reads **Postgres only**, not eAutomate inline.

## Zap UI does not push outbound packing upstream

- **Save lines** / consignment CSV → `outbound_consignment_items` in Zap only.
- **Mark RTD**, transporter, docket → Zap consignment row only.
- **PO line items “Packed Quantity”** on consignment detail = eAutomate `listings_snapshot`, **not** Zap save.

If Save lines succeeds but Packed Quantity stays 0, that is expected unless eAutomate was updated elsewhere.

## Re-sync risks

- Full `sync:outbound-consignment-items` **replaces** consignment items from eAutomate — can wipe Zap packing.
- Prefer `--skip-consignments` on prod for box names + transporters only.

## Prod vs dev

- Sync scripts load `.env.local` (often Tokyo dev) unless `DATABASE_URL` is overridden.
- Prod: `bxgmcddxmlsgrflnbywv` (ap-southeast-2) via `.env.production.local`.

